node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .
.

node.text:
Some people swear by curry only going with white rice but I’m a bit of a rebel. I looove curry with rice & peas! However, if hungry, anything will do! I made some Coconut Curry Salmon with white rice for dinner and currying salmon is one of my favorite ways to enjoy it! Coconut Curry Salmon! Man salmon is one of my favorite fish to eat. I love this recipe because it’s easy to prepare and cooks quickly! Just remember, whenever you curry seafood, it’s always a good idea to cook your curry first before adding the seafood. Seafood cooks very quickly! Grab the recipe in my ebook “Irie Delights” which is now on sale! No code needed. Download at shopthatnursecancook.com (link in bio)

node.text:
Wooyyyy!!! Try nuh hold mi back! Sweet n Sour Chicken wings! That’s how you flip a recipe to meet your needs! I used the recipe for my Sweet n Sour Chicken to make this happen. Instead of diced chicken breasts, I used a bag of party wings. Air fried them to avoid the deep fryer. You can use the recipe or just coat them in cornstarch! I fried about 8 wings at a time on 400 degrees for 30 minutes. 😋 No need to make adjustments to the recipe for the sauce. It’s enough for an entire bag of party wings! Good news!! My ebooks are on SALE this weekend for 25% OFF‼️This recipe is in the Dinner in 30 ebook! Hit the link in my bio to get some good wings started😉
.
.
.
.
.
.

Brown stew chicken wings, yellow rice & peas, fried plantain, and pear! I always feel like brown stew wings are my compromise when I want brown stew chicken but don’t feel like going through the task of cleaning and cutting chicken (my least favorite cooking task). Wings are easy to clean and prepare and perfect on a weeknight! You sharing or nah? 😋

.
.

……there is something special about grabbing a bag of party wings and brown stewing them. Just give me the whole pot! 
.
.
.
.

If you have trouble finding a recipe on youtube simply type thatnursecancook and the dish you’re looking for in youtube’s search bar! 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Nothing like a Caribbean girl 🇯🇲 Drop your flag and let me know which country you’re reppin’. Caribbean girls love them some porridge that’s for sure. I smooth the lumps out in a cup before adding the mixture to the pot because I’m team no lumpy porridge. You can sweeten it with condensed milk if you’re feeling rich, or any sugar you choose. Subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel: thatnursecancook. Recipe video is there 💙 or type thatnursecancook cornmeal porridge into the search if you’re having trouble finding it.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Cmon stop playing and them curry them oxtail! I trim some of the fat on the oxtail so my gravy isn’t too oily. I blend 3 different curries for max flavor: Jamaican Choice, Chief’s, Betapac, and /or Portland Mills. Sometimes I toast the curry, simply depends on what mood I’m in. Makes no difference to me. Once your food is well seasoned and you’ve cooked your oxtail for about 2 hours, that’s more than enough time to fully cook the curry. If you haven’t tried it yet, you’re missing out! Recipe video is on 🎥YouTube: thatnursecancook curry oxtail. The “green stuff”? Youtube: thatnursecancook epis
.
.
.
.
.
.

What do you bring home when you visit your home country? I brought back fried fish, roast breadfruit, some pudding, drops, and gizzada 😎 I fried this breadfruit and had it with brown stew porgy and plantain. I swear enjoying the treats you brought home from vacation is the cherry on top! Hit the link in bio for the recipe and subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel: thatnursecancook
